    "narrative": "The cornerstone of today\u2019s lineup is undoubtedly **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands an elite score of 86.57. With a favorable park factor and a solid matchup against Jacob Lopez, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is the clear anchor, benefiting from both his batting order stability and strong SP skill metrics. Complementing him are **Lawrence Butler** (66.81) and **Will Smith** (66.36); despite his low spot in the order, **Lawrence Butler** receives a massive +13% boost from his platoon advantage against Slade Cecconi, while **Will Smith** leverages a high xwOBA (0.372) and a favorable matchup against Michael McGreevy to maintain his status as a must-start. **Geraldo Perdomo** also earns a prime UTIL spot (64.88) by effectively neutralizing Shota Imanaga, capitalizing on his leadoff placement to drive the scoring ceiling.\n\nThe tightest decision on the board involved **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of the cut at 46.03. While **Matt Chapman** holds inherent value, his matchup against the low-xERA arm of Griffin Jax forced him to the bench in favor of hitters with more favorable platoon splits. We are also monitoring the volatility of a few starts; **Tyler Freeman** faces the formidable Chris Sale (2.99 xERA), creating a high-risk scenario despite his park-adjusted projection. Furthermore, with lineups still pending for **Will Smith**, **Cal Raleigh**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Bryson Stott**, **Masyn Winn**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Gavin Sheets**, **Taylor Ward**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Lawrence Butler**, and **Geraldo Perdomo**, we remain exposed to order shifts that could negate the assumed benefits of their respective spots. **Yainer Diaz** remains a high-variance bench option, with his 45.77 score further dampened by a 33% rain risk, confirming the decision to keep him sidelined.",
